race.comment: MY ANGEL SHELL (6) warmed to his task nicely late when resuming at Terang on December 16. Not as effective last time when left with too much to do at Flemington in a hot BM70. This is much easier and he should relish the rise to 1400m. Leading player. HE'S GODSPEED (2) registered a strong win at Terang two runs ago. Decent effort last time out when finishing a close eighth in a blanket finish. Has started two times at this course and distance and is yet to miss the placings. Have to take seriously. SALSBURY HILL (4) improved sharply on her fourth two starts back at Nhill with a win over 1400m at Penola nine days ago, getting home by a neck. Meeting a deeper field this time but she can give this a shake. THERMODYNAMIC (3) strikes an easier assignment and gets an important claim. Holds hope on best form and is worth including.
